                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184.1 Polk, Frank L.:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-19T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 19, 1919—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3227. Arrival of Mr. Polk will necessitate issuance of new document of
                    appointment and full power for the Commissioners jointly to supersede that of
                    November 30, 1919 [<hi rend="italic">1918</hi>].<note n="70" xml:id="d294fn70"
                        >See <ref target="frus1919Parisv01#pg_175">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>,
                            p. 175</ref>.</note> It is believed that the wording used in the
                    original document will empower Commissioners to sign treaties with Bulgaria and
                    Turkey.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
